.TH "pci_find_next_ext_capability" 9 "pci_find_next_ext_capability" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_find_next_ext_capability \- Find an extended capability
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u16" pci_find_next_ext_capability
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u16 start "  ","
.BI "int cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device to query
.IP "start" 12
address at which to start looking (0 to start at beginning of list)
.IP "cap" 12
capability code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the address of the next matching extended capability structure
within the device's PCI configuration space or 0 if the device does
not support it.  Some capabilities can occur several times, e.g., the
vendor-specific capability, and this provides a way to find them all.
